def: The process of changing into stone; petrification.
That which remains; a remnant; a residue.
A dry slough, crust, or scab, which separates from the healthypart of the body, as that produced by a burn, or the application ofcaustics.
An antiquary; a collector of antiques. [R.] Pinkerton.
A fucus or seaweed much used in the East for soups and jellies;Ceylon moss (Gracilaria lichenoides).
Any declamatory and vociferous preacher or orator.
